1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:53,510 --> 00:01:55,510
What's the matter, Roronoa Zoro?

3
00:01:55,510 --> 00:01:58,470
I can't say for sure,
but you look pretty hurt already.

4
00:01:58,470 --> 00:02:02,440
You think you stand a chance against
my six-sword style in that condition?

5
00:02:02,440 --> 00:02:05,440
The whole world can see
you don't stand a chance.

6
00:02:06,310 --> 00:02:07,940
Keep it to yourself.

7
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:11,440
Big Bro's in rough shape!

8
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:13,700
He's probably feverish
from those wounds.

9
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:15,700
He must be barely conscious.

10
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:20,540
If those wounds open up,
he's definitely going to die!

11
00:02:20,540 --> 00:02:23,080
He doesn't have time
to worry about that, though!

12
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:26,920
Yeah! Big Bro's the only one
who could make it through this!

13
00:02:27,920 --> 00:02:31,130
I'll show you my three-sword style.

14
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:35,430
Yosaku! Johnny!
Give me your swords!

15
00:02:35,430 --> 00:02:36,430
Of course!

16
00:02:36,430 --> 00:02:38,890
Big Bro, catch!

17
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:41,180
Dammit!

18
00:02:41,180 --> 00:02:43,100
I feel like I'm gonna pass out.

19
00:02:43,100 --> 00:02:45,100
How much longer
can I keep this up...?

20
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:47,310
Big Bro! Swords incoming!

21
00:02:47,310 --> 00:02:49,480
You asked for 'em, so catch!

22
00:02:50,110 --> 00:02:54,110
I'll show you the wall that two-armed
humans can't hope to surmount!

23
00:02:54,110 --> 00:02:55,200
Six-Sword Style...

24
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:56,660
Big Bro! Watch out!

25
00:02:56,660 --> 00:02:58,160
...Tentacle Whirligig!

26
00:02:58,160 --> 00:02:59,530
Big Bro!

27
00:03:04,410 --> 00:03:05,500
Three-Sword Style:

28
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:10,800
Floating Wolfblade!

29
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:19,300
He did it!

30
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:22,520
He handled that six-sword
onslaught! He's incredible!

31
00:03:25,770 --> 00:03:28,100
What concentration!

32
00:03:28,100 --> 00:03:30,060
What spirit!

33
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:33,530
Ow... You've got some kind of nerve!

34
00:03:33,900 --> 00:03:36,900
Now I'm pissed off,
you son of a fisherman!

35
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:38,360
I'm gonna kill you!

36
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:41,200
It's so obvious
when you think about it!

37
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:43,540
I have six swords,
and you only have three!

38
00:03:43,540 --> 00:03:46,370
There's no way you
could ever beat me!

39
00:03:46,370 --> 00:03:47,540
Right?!

40
00:03:47,540 --> 00:03:49,040
Obvious, huh?

41
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:51,500
Sounds like a grave miscalculation.

42
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:53,210
What burden do you bear?

43
00:03:53,210 --> 00:03:55,840
What do you seek
in pursuing power, child?

44
00:03:58,050 --> 00:04:02,430
Three swords... Six swords...

45
00:04:02,810 --> 00:04:05,180
The number doesn't matter!

46
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:12,520
It's the weight of our blades
that makes the difference!

47
00:04:19,320 --> 00:04:21,120
He's inhaled a lot of water.

48
00:04:21,120 --> 00:04:23,580
We need to bring him up
soon, or it'll be too late.

49
00:04:25,580 --> 00:04:28,160
Dammit! I can't break it underwater.

50
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:29,830
It's just too buoyant.

51
00:04:29,830 --> 00:04:31,250
Mr. Gen, hurry up.

52
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:33,340
It's no good. I can't smash the rock.

53
00:04:33,340 --> 00:04:36,340
An oxygen tank would help,
but we don't have time to get one.

54
00:04:36,960 --> 00:04:39,720
And we can't carry
both him and the rock...

55
00:04:40,340 --> 00:04:41,430
– That's it!
– That's it!

56
00:04:46,350 --> 00:04:48,140
Weight, you say?

57
00:04:48,140 --> 00:04:52,020
I see. So your swords are heavy.

58
00:04:52,020 --> 00:04:56,440
Believe it or not, each of my swords
weigh over 300 kilograms.

59
00:04:56,440 --> 00:05:01,110
They're much heavier than your
puny human swords, two-arms!

60
00:05:01,660 --> 00:05:04,120
You can't argue with stupid.

61
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:06,580
Six-Sword Style:
Octopus Pot Stance!

62
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,450
New Year's...

63
00:05:10,540 --> 00:05:11,540
Open...

64
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:14,960
Body Slam!

65
00:05:16,090 --> 00:05:17,800
Cheap shot! He hit Big Bro's wounds!

66
00:05:18,170 --> 00:05:19,340
That'll show you!

67
00:05:19,340 --> 00:05:19,880
Big Bro!

68
00:05:20,510 --> 00:05:21,760
He's gonna die!

69
00:05:22,090 --> 00:05:24,140
I'll kill you before you hit the ground!

70
00:05:24,140 --> 00:05:25,260
Six-Sword Style Secret Technique:

71
00:05:25,930 --> 00:05:27,640
Waltz of the Six Swords!

72
00:05:28,100 --> 00:05:30,350
You'll be mincemeat
once you hit my blades!

73
00:05:30,350 --> 00:05:32,060
Ground Zoro coming up!

74
00:05:33,020 --> 00:05:33,980
Big Bro!

75
00:05:41,990 --> 00:05:43,490
Ow!

76
00:05:43,490 --> 00:05:44,990
– Big Bro!
– Big Bro!

77
00:05:52,670 --> 00:05:57,590
That bastard! He timed his roll
in perfect sync with my swords.

78
00:05:57,590 --> 00:06:00,840
What's worse, he threw
in a free hand-cut!

79
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:04,140
How dare he make fun of me!
This isn't some circus act!

80
00:06:04,140 --> 00:06:06,550
That's the last straw!
No one insults me!

81
00:06:06,550 --> 00:06:08,430
Now he's really dead meat!

82
00:06:08,890 --> 00:06:11,930
Big Bro looks like he's in a lot of pain.

83
00:06:11,930 --> 00:06:15,350
That attack must have
opened his wounds.

84
00:06:15,350 --> 00:06:19,150
Ah... I'd trade places
with him if I could...

85
00:06:20,650 --> 00:06:24,700
Even if these wounds would
usually knock someone out...

86
00:06:24,700 --> 00:06:26,910
I must not fall.

87
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:32,910
Six-Sword Style: Octopus Pot Stance!

88
00:06:32,910 --> 00:06:34,290
This is the end for you!

89
00:06:35,750 --> 00:06:39,750
Even if these wounds
would be lethal...

90
00:06:39,750 --> 00:06:41,460
I must not die!

91
00:06:41,460 --> 00:06:42,380
New Year's...

92
00:06:44,340 --> 00:06:46,890
To defeat the
extraordinary Hawk Eye...

93
00:06:48,140 --> 00:06:50,350
I can't just stay ordinary!

94
00:06:56,850 --> 00:06:58,900
Dragon Twister!

95
00:07:17,250 --> 00:07:18,630
Hachi...

96
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:20,840
How could I...

97
00:07:22,210 --> 00:07:24,380
be defeated by...

98
00:07:25,470 --> 00:07:27,260
a three-sword style...?

99
00:07:32,770 --> 00:07:34,140
Octofreak...

100
00:07:35,020 --> 00:07:36,980
now you've learned the difference...

101
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:42,150
between the weight of our blades.

102
00:07:42,150 --> 00:07:43,900
Are you satisfied?

103
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:51,870
Sorry, but that octofreak
doesn't matter now.

104
00:07:52,870 --> 00:07:55,330
I have to hurry and rescue Luffy...

105
00:07:55,330 --> 00:07:56,790
Big Bro! Watch out!

106
00:07:56,790 --> 00:07:58,500
You'll regret what you did to Hachi!

107
00:08:00,460 --> 00:08:01,630
You...

108
00:08:02,170 --> 00:08:04,630
You sure sent me flying!

109
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:06,050
Oh?

110
00:08:06,630 --> 00:08:11,600
I never thought any human
in the East Blue could survive my fist.

111
00:08:12,140 --> 00:08:17,060
I bet there are plenty who could...
especially at a certain restaurant.

112
00:08:18,690 --> 00:08:20,770
You underestimate me.

113
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:23,070
B-Big Bro! That's reckless!

114
00:08:23,070 --> 00:08:24,400
Hey, stop it!

115
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:27,700
You'll die if you jump
in the sea in that condition!

116
00:08:27,700 --> 00:08:31,370
While you're busy talking,
Luffy is drowning!

117
00:08:31,370 --> 00:08:33,450
I can't wait around
for you to finish up.

118
00:08:33,450 --> 00:08:35,160
Yeah, yeah, I got it.

119
00:08:35,750 --> 00:08:38,370
We're on a tight schedule. I got it.

120
00:08:38,370 --> 00:08:40,670
I stopped you because
I know what's at stake.

121
00:08:40,670 --> 00:08:42,630
So save your breath, moron!

122
00:08:43,090 --> 00:08:44,840
You can't complain if I do this, right?!

123
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:48,510
Fascinating!

124
00:08:48,510 --> 00:08:50,630
He wants to fight
a fishman in the water?

125
00:08:50,630 --> 00:08:52,010
What a colossal idiot!

126
00:08:52,010 --> 00:08:53,430
That hothead!

127
00:08:53,430 --> 00:08:57,220
Fighting in the water is
exactly what they want!

128
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:09,780
Oh?

129
00:09:09,780 --> 00:09:11,910
That guy's from Cocoyashi Village!

130
00:09:12,450 --> 00:09:13,660
Is that his neck?

131
00:09:13,660 --> 00:09:15,620
They stretched Luffy's neck!

132
00:09:18,290 --> 00:09:21,170
Sorry, I'm not strong enough
to pull your whole body up.

133
00:09:21,170 --> 00:09:24,920
At least with your head out here,
you can cough up that water and breathe!

134
00:09:25,290 --> 00:09:27,630
Breathe already!
I hope it's not too late!

135
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:29,840
If I don't hurry, I'll run out of air, too!

136
00:09:30,510 --> 00:09:31,800
I see.

137
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:33,340
He can't break the rock,

138
00:09:33,340 --> 00:09:36,970
but they've stretched his head above
water so at least he can breathe.

139
00:09:36,970 --> 00:09:40,060
That means if I can just break
that rock with a kick,

140
00:09:40,060 --> 00:09:41,850
I can leave the rest to him.

141
00:09:41,850 --> 00:09:44,810
Fishman Karate... Forearm Sledge!

142
00:09:47,230 --> 00:09:48,280
Time for a lesson!

143
00:09:48,820 --> 00:09:51,610
You're nothing but humans.

144
00:09:55,950 --> 00:09:58,200
You're from Cocoyashi Village.

145
00:09:58,200 --> 00:09:59,830
You're wasting your time.

146
00:09:59,830 --> 00:10:01,660
Dammit! He found me!

147
00:10:02,040 --> 00:10:05,920
What's the point of
stretching out his life like that?!

148
00:10:05,920 --> 00:10:08,300
I'll sink you as well!

149
00:10:11,260 --> 00:10:12,970
Not if I can help it!

150
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:16,930
You dirty human!

151
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:21,640
Are you seriously trying
to fight me in the water?!

152
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:24,980
The most your inferior species can do is hold its breath!

153
00:10:26,310 --> 00:10:28,400
Have it your way! Let's fight!

154
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:31,820
Fishman Karate: Devil Ray Grappler!

155
00:10:39,490 --> 00:10:41,000
Oh, what's this?

156
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,210
Your kick has half
the force down here.

157
00:10:43,210 --> 00:10:45,710
That's a human limitation.

158
00:10:45,710 --> 00:10:50,500
But being in water doesn't
cripple Fishman Karate!

159
00:10:51,050 --> 00:10:54,430
In fact, some techniques
become twice as powerful!

160
00:10:55,930 --> 00:10:57,390
Fishman Karate:

161
00:10:57,850 --> 00:10:58,680
Blistering...

162
00:10:59,390 --> 00:11:01,640
Bowel Buster!

163
00:11:06,350 --> 00:11:07,650
Fishman Karate:

164
00:11:10,900 --> 00:11:13,860
Flaming Axe Kick!

165
00:11:19,620 --> 00:11:20,990
Back Foot Jawbreaker!

166
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:26,500
Lethal...

167
00:11:28,380 --> 00:11:30,380
Upper Deck Palm Bomb!

168
00:11:52,690 --> 00:11:55,320
Air! Air! Air! Air! Oxygen! Air!

169
00:11:55,740 --> 00:11:57,150
I let out too much air!

170
00:11:57,150 --> 00:11:58,410
I can't breathe!

171
00:12:04,250 --> 00:12:05,580
Where are you going?

172
00:12:05,580 --> 00:12:07,250
Dammit! Let me through.

173
00:12:07,250 --> 00:12:09,670
I need air! Let me breathe!

174
00:12:10,130 --> 00:12:12,500
Your resilience is astonishing...

175
00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:14,130
I can't believe you're human.

176
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:16,470
Let me breathe...

177
00:12:17,590 --> 00:12:19,300
If I remember correctly,

178
00:12:19,300 --> 00:12:23,930
you talked trash about
anyone who would harm a lady.

179
00:12:24,430 --> 00:12:26,060
But look how it's turning out.

180
00:12:26,060 --> 00:12:29,730
This is the outcome
of your worthless chivalry.

181
00:12:32,060 --> 00:12:35,360
You'll die here, unable
to escape from me.

182
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:38,530
That sheriff and the rubber
man are finished, too.

183
00:12:38,530 --> 00:12:44,620
We'll slaughter Zoro, that long-nosed
man, and the rebels from the village.

184
00:12:44,620 --> 00:12:48,580
And after all that, Nami won't
get away with betraying us either!

185
00:12:49,290 --> 00:12:51,000
Do you get it?

186
00:12:51,460 --> 00:12:54,460
Your chivalry is nothing more than lip service,

187
00:12:54,460 --> 00:13:00,220
and it won't protect anyone,
let alone Nami!

188
00:13:06,810 --> 00:13:09,810
You may have some
semblance of strength,

189
00:13:09,810 --> 00:13:14,610
but in the end... it's just
the drivel of a frail human.

190
00:13:16,110 --> 00:13:20,650
You humans can't handle sudden
changes in water pressure, can you?

191
00:13:21,820 --> 00:13:26,200
In other words, if you
rapidly dive into the abyss...

192
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:29,790
your body will burst from the inside.

193
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:36,300
Pulverizing Pressure Plunge!

194
00:13:45,930 --> 00:13:48,220
I'm not gonna let him
get away with this!

195
00:13:48,770 --> 00:13:52,730
He thinks I can't protect anyone?!

196
00:14:06,450 --> 00:14:09,370
He still won't die?

197
00:14:11,620 --> 00:14:15,580
If you want it so badly,
then let's do it again!

198
00:14:16,090 --> 00:14:19,420
They breathe through
their lungs on land,

199
00:14:19,420 --> 00:14:21,970
but they switch to their gills in water.

200
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:28,470
That means he's just
a talking fish right now.

201
00:14:29,970 --> 00:14:32,140
Will you survive it a second time?

202
00:14:32,140 --> 00:14:36,650
A fish will die if air
is forced into its gills.

203
00:14:36,650 --> 00:14:40,400
So this fish oughta
feel the same pain!

204
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:53,410
You...

205
00:14:57,290 --> 00:14:58,170
Hey...

206
00:14:58,170 --> 00:14:59,420
Don't worry.

207
00:14:59,420 --> 00:15:01,050
He's okay.

208
00:15:01,050 --> 00:15:01,840
Really?!

209
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:02,880
Yeah, sort of.

210
00:15:02,880 --> 00:15:04,340
Sort of?

211
00:15:04,340 --> 00:15:05,970
I'll explain later.

212
00:15:06,930 --> 00:15:09,390
Alright, you damn fish!

213
00:15:09,390 --> 00:15:11,220
Come out here, and let's finish this!

214
00:15:14,480 --> 00:15:17,190
You still don't get it, do you?

215
00:15:17,190 --> 00:15:21,610
Whether it's in the water
or on land, it's all the same.

216
00:15:21,610 --> 00:15:23,740
I'm furious!

217
00:15:24,110 --> 00:15:27,410
I'll demonstrate the very
essence of Fishman Karate!

218
00:15:28,620 --> 00:15:32,660
The attack that sent you flying
earlier was the hundred tile fist!

219
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:37,250
But my ultimate attack
is the thousand tile fist!

220
00:15:37,250 --> 00:15:39,420
Your probability of surviving...

221
00:15:39,420 --> 00:15:42,920
is zero!

222
00:15:43,960 --> 00:15:44,720
Collier!

223
00:15:48,640 --> 00:15:50,800
My chivalry is worthless?

224
00:15:52,260 --> 00:15:53,890
Épaule!

225
00:15:54,890 --> 00:15:57,600
I can't protect anyone, you said?

226
00:15:57,600 --> 00:16:01,400
Côtelette! Selle! Poitrine!

227
00:16:01,770 --> 00:16:03,730
Gigot!

228
00:16:07,990 --> 00:16:10,120
You son of a...

229
00:16:10,740 --> 00:16:11,700
Son of a bitch!

230
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:15,290
Ultimate Fist: Thousand Tiles!

231
00:16:20,380 --> 00:16:21,590
Mouton...

232
00:16:21,590 --> 00:16:22,460
Shot!

233
00:16:41,810 --> 00:16:43,270
I guess...

234
00:16:44,320 --> 00:16:45,940
he doesn't want dessert?

235
00:17:01,170 --> 00:17:03,040
Kuroobi...

236
00:17:05,550 --> 00:17:06,920
Hachi...

237
00:17:07,760 --> 00:17:10,220
They were minnows, after all.

238
00:17:10,220 --> 00:17:13,600
A fish taking on a cook?
Not in a million years.

239
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:16,010
This game...

240
00:17:16,560 --> 00:17:18,560
goes to us.

241
00:17:20,060 --> 00:17:27,360
How dare you bastards beat my
sworn brothers one after another...

242
00:17:27,360 --> 00:17:31,410
Who do you whelps think you are?!

243
00:17:34,660 --> 00:17:38,870
So, what'd you mean by
Luffy being "sort of" okay?

244
00:17:38,870 --> 00:17:42,000
It means that he's not
dying at the moment.

245
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:46,460
But to bring him all the way back,
I gotta dive down one more time...

246
00:17:47,460 --> 00:17:51,340
though it doesn't seem like
that guy's gonna let me...

247
00:17:54,300 --> 00:17:56,890
Wow! They really are amazing!

248
00:17:57,680 --> 00:18:00,430
They beat two of Arlong's officers!

249
00:18:04,900 --> 00:18:07,730
That's all I can do. I can't
hold my breath any longer.

250
00:18:07,730 --> 00:18:10,690
Mr. Gen, take my place.
I'll go in this time.

251
00:18:10,690 --> 00:18:12,490
He's coughed up a lot of water.

252
00:18:12,490 --> 00:18:13,740
What about the others?

253
00:18:13,740 --> 00:18:16,120
Don't worry. Everyone's still alive.

254
00:18:16,120 --> 00:18:17,240
In fact...

255
00:18:17,740 --> 00:18:19,750
I can barely believe it,

256
00:18:19,750 --> 00:18:22,040
but this fight has reawakened...

257
00:18:22,660 --> 00:18:25,460
the hope I thought was gone...!

258
00:18:32,050 --> 00:18:35,090
Sheesh... You caused
me a lot of trouble!

259
00:18:35,840 --> 00:18:38,510
You sure are good at running away!

260
00:18:40,100 --> 00:18:41,810
But that was too easy.

261
00:18:41,810 --> 00:18:44,690
All it took to kill you is
one shot of my Water Gun.

262
00:18:46,020 --> 00:18:49,940
Guess I should head back.
The others should be done by now.

263
00:18:51,650 --> 00:18:52,990
I'm saved!

264
00:18:53,320 --> 00:18:58,870
It worked! I'm so glad I made the
ketchup star for times like this.

265
00:18:58,870 --> 00:19:02,450
He thinks his Water Gun
or whatever actually hit me.

266
00:19:03,120 --> 00:19:04,580
Go home, loser!

267
00:19:06,420 --> 00:19:10,500
Man, talk about a scary race...

268
00:19:10,840 --> 00:19:15,630
They turned the houses
in town upside down!

269
00:19:16,220 --> 00:19:22,640
Well, I feel sorry for Nami,
and I really want to help her, but...

270
00:19:26,140 --> 00:19:27,690
Just my imagination...

271
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:30,900
I think I'll pass on dying.

272
00:19:31,690 --> 00:19:35,900
B-But now I that think about it,
even with all this fake blood,

273
00:19:35,900 --> 00:19:39,780
I need to look a little more
roughed up... Like I fought bravely...

274
00:19:39,780 --> 00:19:41,450
Oh, I know!

275
00:19:41,450 --> 00:19:45,040
If I show up covered in dirt,
it'll probably look that way.

276
00:19:45,040 --> 00:19:49,750
I'll say something like,
"Ah, sorry. I lost."

277
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:53,260
Hmm... Maybe it's better as:

278
00:19:53,260 --> 00:19:58,180
"Well, that bastard slipped away,
but I was so close!"

279
00:19:58,180 --> 00:20:01,220
No, they won't fall for that...

280
00:20:01,760 --> 00:20:03,970
You're one of us now, aren't you?

281
00:20:04,350 --> 00:20:09,400
"Hey, don't cry, Nami.
We only did what was right."

282
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:12,610
I'd rather die than lose.

283
00:20:12,610 --> 00:20:16,450
"Well, we all put up a good fight."

284
00:20:16,780 --> 00:20:21,780
But he's a hundred times better than
a bunch of thugs who'd hurt a lady.

285
00:20:22,530 --> 00:20:25,750
"Well, it certainly was
a battle to the death."

286
00:20:26,290 --> 00:20:28,210
I have a job to finish!

287
00:20:28,210 --> 00:20:30,460
This was my only choice!

288
00:20:31,710 --> 00:20:36,340
"Well, my injuries aren't that bad."

289
00:20:36,340 --> 00:20:38,760
Big Sis Nami was crying!

290
00:20:38,760 --> 00:20:42,300
What other reason do they need
to put their lives on the line?

291
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:44,720
Nami was only ten.

292
00:20:44,720 --> 00:20:47,270
Can you imagine how hard
of a choice that was?

293
00:20:49,230 --> 00:20:52,150
– We'll fight!
– We'll fight!

294
00:20:56,740 --> 00:21:03,160
"Well, the way...
I fought... was really..."

295
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:08,370
How...

296
00:21:09,660 --> 00:21:11,330
How pathetic...!

297
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:20,380
How could I be so pathetic?!

298
00:21:20,380 --> 00:21:23,220
Hold it, you damn fish!

299
00:21:25,260 --> 00:21:28,850
Oh? You're still alive?

300
00:21:30,690 --> 00:21:32,150
You got that right!

301
00:21:32,150 --> 00:21:35,070
As if some half-fish could
hit me with a wild shot!

302
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:41,660
The moment I left my village,
I said goodbye...

303
00:21:41,660 --> 00:21:44,240
to peace and safety.

304
00:21:45,030 --> 00:21:47,490
They live like there's no tomorrow!

305
00:21:47,490 --> 00:21:50,790
That's why they can laugh so happily!

306
00:21:53,250 --> 00:21:55,920
That's why I decided
to set out to the sea.

307
00:21:55,920 --> 00:21:57,880
I wanted to laugh like that too!

308
00:21:57,880 --> 00:22:00,340
If I don't fight with everything I've got,

309
00:22:00,340 --> 00:22:03,890
then I'm not worthy to be on
board the same ship as them!

310
00:22:03,890 --> 00:22:08,180
I won't have the right
to laugh along with them!

311
00:22:17,650 --> 00:22:19,030
Are you an idiot?

312
00:22:19,860 --> 00:22:21,990
You should've just kept playing dead.

313
00:22:22,780 --> 00:22:25,490
Even your brain is inferior.

314
00:22:27,160 --> 00:22:30,790
I'm done...

315
00:22:31,160 --> 00:22:32,580
Yeah, you are!

316
00:22:32,580 --> 00:22:34,620
You're done for, alright!

317
00:22:35,130 --> 00:22:36,330
I'm done!

318
00:22:36,880 --> 00:22:38,340
Usopp Hammer!

319
00:22:40,050 --> 00:22:42,300
Usopp's Rubber Band of Doom!

320
00:22:47,850 --> 00:22:49,350
Dammit!

321
00:22:49,350 --> 00:22:52,520
I fell for that stupid trick!

322
00:22:53,020 --> 00:22:56,900
Why, that dirty...!

323
00:22:59,320 --> 00:23:01,900
Lethal Lead Star!

324
00:23:00,070 --> 00:23:01,150
Alcohol?

325
00:23:04,820 --> 00:23:09,080
I've had enough of your cowardly
tricks, you insolent worm!

326
00:23:09,780 --> 00:23:14,660
No matter where you hide,
I'll blast you with this water!

327
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:20,800
I don't care if he calls me
cowardly or insolent...

328
00:23:20,800 --> 00:23:25,510
If I want to be a man,
I can't run from this fight.

329
00:23:26,260 --> 00:23:28,470
If I lose, I'm dead.

330
00:23:28,470 --> 00:23:30,970
I'm a pirate now!

331
00:23:30,970 --> 00:23:32,430
Water Cannon!

332
00:23:41,400 --> 00:23:42,530
Wow!

333
00:23:42,530 --> 00:23:44,610
That really packs a punch!

334
00:23:45,360 --> 00:23:49,320
Why do I have to fight
such an idiot?

335
00:23:49,700 --> 00:23:52,080
He's completely exposed!

336
00:23:53,080 --> 00:23:54,790
I'm gonna riddle you with holes!

337
00:23:54,790 --> 00:23:57,000
Water Machine Gun!

338
00:23:58,290 --> 00:24:00,960
H-How did he
figure out where I was?!

339
00:24:00,960 --> 00:24:02,340
Dammit! Dammit!

340
00:24:02,340 --> 00:24:05,590
Just watch me,
Usopp Pirates and Kaya!

341
00:24:05,590 --> 00:24:08,050
I set off to sea and became a pirate!

342
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:09,800
I'll fight!

343
00:24:09,800 --> 00:24:14,470
I'll become a brave warrior
of the sea for real! No more lies!

344
00:24:14,470 --> 00:24:22,360
I'm done fooling around and
pretending to be a pirate!

345
00:24:23,360 --> 00:24:24,990
What did you say was done?

346
00:24:24,990 --> 00:24:27,700
This fight! Alcohol catches
on fire, you know!

347
00:24:28,240 --> 00:24:30,450
Lethal Fire Star!

348
00:24:35,160 --> 00:24:36,290
Hot! Hot! Hot!

349
00:24:36,290 --> 00:24:39,120
Water! Water! Water!
Water! Water! Water!

350
00:24:39,120 --> 00:24:40,710
Hot! Hot! Hot!

351
00:24:40,210 --> 00:24:40,710
Uh-oh!

352
00:24:40,710 --> 00:24:43,710
Water, water, water! Water!

353
00:24:44,750 --> 00:24:48,170
Usopp Hammer!

354
00:25:09,450 --> 00:25:10,160
D-Damn you...!

355
00:25:10,160 --> 00:25:10,780
Ugh!

356
00:25:11,280 --> 00:25:12,570
Usopp Hammer!

357
00:25:12,570 --> 00:25:13,450
Usopp Hammer!

358
00:25:13,450 --> 00:25:14,330
Usopp Hammer!

359
00:25:14,330 --> 00:25:15,540
Usopp Hammer!

360
00:25:15,540 --> 00:25:16,870
Usopp's Rubber Band of Doom!

361
00:25:16,870 --> 00:25:17,790
Usopp Hammer!

362
00:25:17,790 --> 00:25:18,750
Usopp Hammer!

363
00:25:18,750 --> 00:25:20,790
Usopp Hammer!

364
00:25:29,470 --> 00:25:32,390
I win! I beat a fishman!

365
00:25:38,480 --> 00:25:40,850
Serves you right!

366
00:25:40,850 --> 00:25:43,610
I can do it, too, if I try!

367
00:25:43,610 --> 00:25:45,860
Did you see that?!

368
00:25:45,860 --> 00:25:49,110
Don't underestimate
me, you bastards!
